1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on utilizing multiple radio interfaces to increase wireless data throughput in heterogeneous networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The use of network coding to increase throughput is a topic within information theory.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with improving wireless communication in heterogeneous networks, which is a topic within communications and networking.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system-level approach to improve wireless data throughput, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the ability to efficiently process large amounts of data, which is a topic within multimedia.
